The paper deals with the computational complexity of algebraic models, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The use of Weihrauch reducibility, a tool for analyzing the computational content of mathematical theorems, suggests that it could also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The study of topological aspects of computation models could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Scientific Computing (cs.SC) categories. Finally, the mention of computable analysis suggests that it could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category.
